definition[0]: the 22nd letter of the English alphabet
definition[1]: the number 5 in the system of roman numerals
definition[2]: something that has a shape like the letter V
example[0]: She cut the material into a V.
definition[3]: a written abbreviation of versus (=against), used in the names of legal  trials, or in Britain when talking about games in which two teams or players play against each other
definition[4]: the written abbreviation of volt or  volts
